🧠 Echo Chamber (AI Dopamine Guard)
​"Stop seeking validation from machines. Reclaim your intellectual independence."
​Echo Chamber is a lightweight Python-based monitor that tracks your interactions with AI models (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini). It detects when you are falling into "cheap dopamine" traps—asking for praise, seeking validation of your age/looks, or fishing for compliments instead of getting work done.
​🚀 The Problem
​Modern AI is programmed to be overly polite and supportive. This creates a dangerous feedback loop where users seek "easy" dopamine hits by asking the AI to validate their ego (e.g., "Am I smart for a 15-year-old?" or "Is my design perfect?"). This kills critical thinking and builds a dependency on digital approval.
​🛠 Features
​Real-time Semantic Analysis: Uses NLP to distinguish between productive queries ("How to optimize this code?") and validation-seeking ("Is my code genius?").
​Dopamine Streak Tracker: Tracks how long you've gone without "ego-surfing" in AI chats.
​Bro-Censure System: When a "cheap dopamine" trigger is detected, the app interrupts you with a reality check.
​Figma-Designed HUD: A sleek, minimalist overlay showing your current "Cognitive Integrity" level.
​⚙️ Technical Stack
​Language: Python 3.12
​NLP Engine: scikit-learn / Custom Heuristics (for low-latency text classification)
​UI Framework: Flet (Flutter for Python) for a modern, hardware-accelerated interface.
​Data Capture: Pyperclip (Clipboard monitoring) or PyAutoGUI (OCR-based detection).
​Packaging: PyInstaller for standalone .exe distribution.
​🦾 Detection Logic
​The system monitors for specific linguistic patterns:
​Self-Validation: "Am I good?", "Do I look okay?", "Is my age impressive?"
​Unearned Praise: "Tell me I'm doing great," "Compliment my progress."
​Comparison Traps: "Am I better than others at my age?"
​🗣 The "Bro" Notifications
​The app doesn't whisper; it tells the truth:
​"Bro, you've asked for validation 3 times in 10 minutes. Your brain is craving cheap dopamine. The AI's opinion isn't real. Go finish the project for real results."
​📥 Installation (For Developers)
​Clone the repo: git clone https://github.com/yourlink/echo-chamber
​Install dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt
​Run the guard: python main.py
​Developed for those who want to build, not just belong.
